And the moment we only send invitation posts with only text, but in original https://github.com/konard/vk-bot we used to send current active avatar of the user, we need to find a way to reproduce the same feature, so not only text message should be in post, but also current active avatar of the user. That will attract more attention from real users, and will provide additional likes to the avatar itself.

Also for each community we need to record in our .lino files in the application folder previously existing wall posts, so post ids should be saved, so if we see there is no our invitation posts in top 10 posts once in 15 minutes (or use repeat interval from https://github.com/konard/vk-bot as it is better tuned) we should delete our previous posts, as they are unlikely to be seen, and post new posts. The logic should be as intelligent as it was in https://github.com/konard/vk-bot, because for communites with less frequent updated, there is no need to create more posts than needed. And also we should keep our post on top, but not more than 1 post at a time, so we should record previously send posts, so once the we send new one, we can delete previous, and remove it from the .lino file. So we deleted post successfully we remove it from .lino file as expected, to not grow the file too much. And also each next new post is added to .lino file.

